# 🏆 Agent Benchmarking — Master Implementation Plan

> **Project Goal:** Benchmark two distinct RAG agent architectures (Naive RAG vs. Corrective Agentic RAG) on a large-scale QA dataset (1,500+ queries) using multi-dimensional evaluation, and produce a rigorous, publication-grade benchmark report with visualizations.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This plan is designed to **stand out against competing submissions**. Key differentiators:
> 1. **Corrective RAG (CRAG)** — not just "simple vs. agentic", but a research-backed self-correcting architecture
> 2. **Dual dataset strategy** — both single-hop AND multi-hop questions to expose architectural limits
> 3. **Multi-dimensional metrics** — Accuracy, Faithfulness, Latency, Cost, Retrieval Quality (6+ metrics)
> 4. **LLM-as-a-Judge + Quantitative** — hybrid evaluation combining F1/EM with GPT-4o judging
> 5. **Component-level tracing** — per-node analysis showing WHERE each system fails

---

## 📐 Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Benchmark Pipeline"
        A[Dataset Loader] --> B[Query Dispatcher]
        B --> C1[Agent A: Naive RAG]
        B --> C2[Agent B: Corrective Agentic RAG]
        C1 --> D[Result Collector]
        C2 --> D
        D --> E[Evaluation Engine]
        E --> F1[Quantitative Metrics]
        E --> F2[LLM-as-a-Judge]
        F1 --> G[Analysis & Visualization]
        F2 --> G
        G --> H[Benchmark Report]
    end
```

